OL,3,CTributes for 'tenacious campaigner'
OL,4,Cwho set up leading HIV charity
OL,6,FTributes have been paid to the founder
OL,7,Fof a leading HIV/Aids charity who has
OL,8,Fdied, aged 71.
OL,10,FNewport-born Martyn Butler co-founded
OL,11,Fthe Terrence Higgins Trust in 1982
OL,12,Fafter the death of his friend Terry `
OL,13,Fthe first person to die of Aids in the
OL,14,FUK.
OL,16,FAlong with Mr Higgins' boyfriend,
OL,17,FRupert Whitaker, Mr Butler established
OL,18,Fthe charity to support people living
OL,19,Fwith Aids and share information about
OL,20,Fpreventing the transmission of HIV.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/8
